  "text": "Epigenetic processes can stably alter gene transcriptional activities independently of the DNA sequence. Several biochemical mechanisms that lead to changes in DNA methylation and/or histone modifications have been discovered to be involved in the processes [CITATION_1] . DNA methylation is important for diverse epigenetic phenomena in plants, including repression of transposable elements (TEs) and repetitive sequences and genomic imprinting.",
